verbose_text: Whereas the mRNA levels of APA [194% (177; 248), P < 0.01] and IRAP [151% (143; 185), P < 0.01] were already elevated in response to 11 mM or higher concentrations of glucose, APN mRNA levels [130% (116; 179), P < 0.01] were significantly upregulated from starting from the concentration of 15 mM glucose.
